GIT CONFIGURATION IN LOCALHOST

1. Launch EC2 Instacne 
		with RED-HAT operating system
		
2. Login the Ec2  with putty.exe
	
	Use  .ppk key for windows  
                  (or) 
	 User  .pem key for Linux 
	 
3. Run the below command in the Instance

	sudo su
	yum update -y
	
4. GIT  installation steps
		yum install git -y
		git version
		
5.  GIT CONFIGURATION
     git config --global user.name "XXXXX"
	 git config --global user.email "XXXXX@ gmail.com"
	 git config --global push.detail simple
	 
6. CHECK GIT CONFIGURATION
	git config --list

7.  GIT CLONE WITH MASTER STEPS
		Create directory  
				mkdir <give any name>
		initiate the directory as git repository  (be inside the created directory)
				git init  --bare
				
		create a file inside the directory
				touch <file name>
		check status of the created file
				git status
		add the file to statging area
				git add
		commit the file to local repository
				git commit -m "commit message"
8. CLONE THE GIT REPOSITORY

			git clone "get the link from the repository"  (which is shown in right side of the repository clone/download button)

9. PUSH THE FILE TO GIT HUB

       git push -u orgin master
	   or 
	   git push origin master
	   
	   

		
		
		